column1: Inspirit Seungkwan lets go &lt

Here after watching the last episode of Nana Tour... I can't thank NaPD and all of the staff enough on how much they've taken care of the boys and gave them a healing trip. It wasn't easy to take all 12 of then plus all the staff but they managed to make a very good show. We all laugh, learn, cry, and heal at the same time... They never even missed mentioning SCoups every single episode. The boys themselves are genuinely happy that we cannot say our thanks enough for this. We all know that it was also a very crucial moment for them considering how busy they were and how some members were physically and mentally exhausted, this was the best feeling ever. Even though Scoups cannot be there, we can see how he was just so happy that his members was able to get the healing they needed while he focus on his recovery to be able to come back. Thank you once again <3

OMG this was insane 😂 I think Na PD didn't account for what it meant to have 13 guests! I'm procrastinating studying so I'm calculating probabilities...I've never been good at math so correct me if they are wrong or ignore them, it's ok lol! ⤵

➡ Probability of Joshua drawing 1 winning ballot out of a bag with 66 ballots (6 out of 66 ballots contain a prize) 6/66 = 0.0909^ or 9% probability.
➡ Probability of DK drawing 1 winning ballot out of a bag with 65 ballots (6 out of 65 ballots contain a prize): 6/65 = 0.0923 or 9.2% probability.🌟

math time!

6 wishes out of 66 total cards, with 3+3+1+3+5 = 15 total picks. The chance of them getting no wishes at all was about (60 choose 15)/(66 choose 15) = 19.8%.

Meanwhile, there was a 6*(60 choose 14)/(66 choose 15) = 37.8% chance of them getting 1 wish, 15*(60 choose 13)/(66 choose 15) = 28.9% chance of them getting 2 wishes, 20*(60 choose 12)/(66 choose 15) = 10.4% chance of them getting 3 wishes, 15*(60 choose 11)/(66 choose 15) = 1.9% chance of them getting 4 wishes, 0.1% chance of them getting 5 wishes, and <0.1% chance of them getting all 6.

of course this doesn't tell us anything about youth over flowers specifically, but just the fact that they picked 3+ prizes is already amazing!

(it's been a while so my math may be inaccurate...)
